Dependencies:
    Python 2.6:
        (either run as root or inside a virtualenv)
        pip install celery
        pip install django
        pip install django-celery
    EXPERIMENTAL:
        pip install stomp.py (for experimental chat)
        pip install orbited for server push chat

    RabbitMQ


Use manage.py to set up your dev environment or the supplied setup-devdb.sh script

./manage.py syncdb --noinput

To load a set of fake test users:
./manage.py loaddata test_users_participants

To load a set of forestry test data:
./manage.py loaddata forestry_test_data

To start celery properly for task scheduling, you'll need to start both a celeryd
and celerybeat, e.g.,

./manage.py celeryd
./manage.py celerybeat
